Update the processedData useMemo filter logic to apply time-based filtering for closed tasks.

## Implementation
In App.tsx processedData useMemo (lines 72-104):

1. Create helper function to check if bead passes time filter:
```typescript
const passesClosedTimeFilter = (bead: Bead) => {
  if (bead.status !== 'closed') return true; // only filter closed tasks
  if (closedTimeFilter === 'all') return true;
  if (!bead.closed_at) return true; // no timestamp, include it

  const closedDate = new Date(bead.closed_at);
  const now = new Date();
  const hoursAgo = (now.getTime() - closedDate.getTime()) / (1000 * 60 * 60);

  switch(closedTimeFilter) {
    case '1h': return hoursAgo <= 1;
    case '6h': return hoursAgo <= 6;
    case '24h': return hoursAgo <= 24;
    case '7d': return hoursAgo <= 168;
    case '30d': return hoursAgo <= 720;
    case 'older_than_6h': return hoursAgo > 6;
    // etc
    default: return true;
  }
};
```

2. Apply filter in the beads.filter() call alongside hideClosed check
3. Update hideClosed logic to work with time filter (both should be AND conditions)

